Description: PhilanTrack is an online grants management system designed to address this inefficiency and help social sector organizations.
Headquarters Regions: Washington DC Metro Area, Southern US
Full Description: 13% of every foundation grant dollar is spent on grants administration. That means thirteen cents on every dollar given to nonprofits  over $6 billion annually  is not being spent on service delivery. That amounts to a lot of missed opportunities for impact.  PhilanTrack is an online grants management system designed to address this inefficiency and help social sector organizations get maximum social impact.  Grant funding is an essential factor in the operations of many nonprofits. In the current economy, more than ever, nonprofits are struggling to deliver valuable products and services to people and communities in need. The organizations that fund nonprofits are looking for the most effective ways to make funding decisions, and to evaluate the impact of their donations. That's why we created PhilanTrack.  The PhilanTrack online grants management system helps both funders and nonprofits streamline the grants management process and maximize social impact. This leading grants administration system centralizes and streamlines grant proposals, reports, and overall management and enables valuable resources to be redirected toward service delivery and greater social impact.  When you know more about it, youll understand why we say PhilanTrack is the future of grants management, helping all partners in the funding equation to maximize impact with good information.

Description: Heavy equipment telematics company made by equipment owners for equipment owners
Headquarters Regions: Greater Minneapolis-Saint Paul Area, Great Lakes, Midwestern US
Full Description: Clear Telematics was founded by materials handling equipment distributors who sought to harness the power of GPS telematics technology to better manage their extensive fleet of over 1,500 industrial machines. Their journey began with the challenges they faced in the North Dakota oil fields, where misplacing a unit or not tracking its runtime could result in several additional hours of travel. Their quest for a suitable telematics solution led them to try five different companies, but none met their expectations in terms of affordability and compatibility with their diverse fleet. Dissatisfied with the available options, they took matters into their own hands and crafted the telematics system they had envisioned. This system, Clear Telematics, is a GPS telematics device paired with fleet monitoring software, tailored to meet the practical needs of equipment owners without breaking the bank. What sets Clear Telematics apart is its affordability compared to other IoT fleet management solutions and its user-friendly design. Users can monitor vehicles, equipment, and machinery from various manufacturers all on a single dashboard. This includes heavy machinery, construction equipment, and commercial vans. Additionally, Clear Telematics offers an open API, allowing businesses to integrate their telematics data with their existing management software. The system is designed to be straightforward and durable, avoiding unnecessary features that could complicate the user experience and increase costs. At its core, Clear Telematics aims to provide essential data at a price point that ensures a tangible return on investment for its users.

Description: iCattleMgrPro is a developer of smartphone applications designed for agriculture and livestock management
Headquarters Regions: Dallas/Fort Worth Metroplex, Southern US
Full Description: iCattleMgrPro is a developer of smartphone applications designed for agriculture and livestock management.The company's application offers the ability to input data such as animal identification, name, gender, sire/dam/surrogate, birth date, birth weight, breeder, weaning date/weight, photo/PDF email, GPS information and pasture management enabling cattlemen, farmers and ranchers to monitor and manage their herds more efficiently.  The company locally owned and operated in Weatherford TX, initially focused on fitness and healthcare utilities. They soon found themselves involved in the rapidly developing agriculture and livestock management application genre. The first of the series was iCattleMgr, (formerly named iCattleLog). Originally built as a prototype to replace handwritten log books that keep track of show cattle. When version 1.0 was released in iTunes they quickly realized that there is a dire need for applications like this for the agriculture industry. The response was exciting, they received numerous request for enhancements and struggled to keep up with demand. Because of this they realized the initial prototype design would not be flexible enough to keep up with request for enhancements. A standard architecture was then implemented and released with iLivestockMgr and later iCattleMgrPro and finally iCattleMgr was converted with an update.

Through networks of independent insurance agents in Louisiana, Mississippi, Arkansas, and Tennessee, LEMIC provided workers' compensation coverage.
